cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.MA 

The paper deals with the problem of resource allocation in multi-agent settings, which is a fundamental problem in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The first part of the paper focuses on agents expressing additive cardinal utilities over objects, which is a topic in decision theory and optimization (cs.DS). The second part of the paper deals with agents expressing ordinal preferences over single objects, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG) as well as multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
